<paragraph id="2D2A36B0FF9EFFA9FCBDAB54FC35FE2E" blockId="7.[809,1420,160,772]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">
<emphasis id="1FE1EAA2FF9EFFA9FCBDAB54FC28FE86" bold="true" box="[810,971,300,324]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Identification.</emphasis>
This is the only species of the genus in 
<collectingCountry id="55827620FF9EFFA9FCBDAB36FC9CFEA4" box="[810,895,334,358]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. It is a medium-sized cat, with a short tail and red or grayish dorsal pelage. The underparts are white with black spots. Ears have pointed tufts, and the hair on sides of head are long (
<bibRefCitation id="49044B41FF9EFFA9FB89ABCBFAA2FE09" author="Lariviere S &amp; Walton LR" box="[1054,1345,435,459]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref10354" refString="Lariviere S, Walton LR (1997) Lynx rufus. Mammalian Species 563: 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3504533" type="journal article" year="1997">Larivière and Walton 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="49044B41FF9EFFA9FADBABCBFC29FE2E" author="Loveless AM &amp; Reding DM &amp; Kapfer PM &amp; Papes M" pageId="7" pageNumber="676" pagination="842 - 857" refId="ref10720" refString="Loveless AM, Reding DM, Kapfer PM, Papes M (2016) Combining ecological niche modelling and morphology to assess the rangewide population genetic structure of bobcats (Lynx rufus). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society 117: 842 - 857. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / bij. 12718" type="journal article" year="2016">Loveless et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="658F653BFF9EFFA9FCBDAB83FB98FDBB" pageId="7" pageNumber="676" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2D2A36B0FF9EFFA9FCBDAB83FB98FDBB" blockId="7.[809,1420,160,772]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">
<emphasis id="1FE1EAA2FF9EFFA9FCBDAB83FC5DFDD1" bold="true" box="[810,958,507,531]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southern 
<collectingCountry id="55827620FF9EFFA9FBA4AB84FB6BFDD6" box="[1075,1160,508,532]" name="Canada" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Canada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="55827620FF9EFFA9FB02AB84FB2FFDD6" box="[1173,1228,508,532]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">USA</collectingCountry>
, through most of northern and central 
<collectingCountry id="55827620FF9EFFA9FB8DA865FB8FFDF7" box="[1050,1132,541,565]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to the TMVB (
<bibRefCitation id="49044B41FF9EFFA9FAB2A865FC0AFD95" author="Lariviere S &amp; Walton LR" pageId="7" pageNumber="676" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref10354" refString="Lariviere S, Walton LR (1997) Lynx rufus. Mammalian Species 563: 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3504533" type="journal article" year="1997">Larivière and Walton 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Recorded habitats in 
<collectingRegion id="EF51F852FF9EFFA9FB7CA847FA82FD95" box="[1259,1377,575,599]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
are quebradas, sierras, and valleys.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="658F653BFF9EFFA9FCBDA8F0FAABFCC6" pageId="7" pageNumber="676" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2D2A36B0FF9EFFA9FCBDA8F0FAABFCC6" blockId="7.[809,1420,160,772]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">
<emphasis id="1FE1EAA2FF9EFFA9FCBDA8F0FC7AFD62" bold="true" box="[810,921,648,672]" pageId="7" pageNumber="676">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is a common felid inhabiting most of the state (
<bibRefCitation id="49044B41FF9EFFA9FC7BA8D1FC82FD21" author="Lopez-Gonzalez C &amp; Garcia-Mendoza D" pageId="7" pageNumber="676" pagination="1122 - 1133" refId="ref10434" refString="Lopez-Gonzalez C, Garcia-Mendoza D (2012) A checklist of the mammals (Mammalia) of Chihuahua, Mexico. Check List 8 (6): 1122 - 1133. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 8.6.1122" type="journal article" year="2012">López-González and García-Mendoza 2012</bibRefCitation>
), even in urban and semi-urban areas. However, it is rarely observed in the sierras because of its habits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
